    "en": {
      "title": "Changes in electricity consumption in Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Public Utilities Commission Chairman Janaka Ratnayake said the country's electricity consumption has dropped by more than 20% in the past two months.",
        "He pointed out that the daily power consumption rate is at least 48 MW and 2,800 MW is required for peak hours.",
        "In the last two months, power consumption was between 38 and 40 MW. \u201cThe peak power demand has come down to 2,100 MW,\u201d he said."
      ],
